from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import numpy as np
import time

Property_name = [] 
Property_type = []
Price= []
Configuration=[]
Area = []
Status = []
Facing = []
Floor = []
total_time = time.time()

for i in range(1, 200): 
    start_time = time.time()
    URL = f"https://www.squareyards.com/sale/apartments-for-sale-in-hyderabad?page={i}"
    page = requests.get(URL)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.text, "html.parser")

    for x in soup.find_all('div', attrs={'class':'listing-body'}):
        pname = x.find('span', attrs={'class':'project-name'})
        ptype= x.find('h2', attrs={'class':'heading'})   
        price = x.find('p', attrs={'class':'listing-price'})
        config= x.find('em', attrs={'class':'icon-bed'})
        area = x.find('span', attrs={'class':'unit-value avail-area'})
        status = x.find('em', attrs={'class':'icon-project-status'})
        facing = x.find('em', attrs={'class':'icon-remedies'})
        floor = x.find('em', attrs={'class':'icon-stairs'})
       
        
    
 
        
        
        Property_name.append(pname.text if pname else np.nan)
        Property_type.append(ptype.text if ptype else np.nan)
        Price.append(price.text if price else np.nan)
        Configuration.append(config.find_next('span').text.strip() if config and config.find_next('span') else np.nan)
        Area.append(area.text.strip() if area else np.nan)
        Status.append(status.find_next('span').text.strip() if status and status.find_next('span') else np.nan)
        Facing.append(facing.find_next('span').text.strip() if facing and facing.find_next('span') else np.nan)
        Floor.append(floor.find_next('span').text.strip() if floor and floor.find_next('span') else np.nan)
        
       
        


    print(f'Page {i} completed in {time.time()-start_time:.2f} seconds')

print("Total Time Completed in seconds", str(time.time()-total_time))

#price column cleaning
df['Price'] = df['Price'].str.extract(
    r'(\s*[\d\.]+\s*(?:[Cc][Rr]|[Ll])(?:\s*-\s*?\s*[\d\.]+\s*(?:[Cc][Rr]|[Ll]))?)'
)

df['Price'] = (
    df['Price']
    .str.replace('', '', regex=False)
    .str.replace(r'\s+', '', regex=True)
    .str.strip()
)



#area column cleaning
df['Area'] = (
    df['Area']
    .str.replace(r'\s+', ' ', regex=True)   
    .str.strip()                            
    .str.replace(r'\.$', '', regex=True)  
)


#Floor column cleaning
df['Floor'] = (
    df['Floor']
    .str.replace(r'\s+', ' ', regex=True)        
    .str.strip()                                 
    .str.replace(r'(\d+)(?:th|st|nd|rd)?\s*$', r'\1th Floor', regex=True)  
)

#Property_type column cleaning
df['Property_type'] = df['Property_type'].str.replace(r'\s+', ' ', regex=True).str.strip()

sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid", font_scale=0.9)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

pair = sns.pairplot(
    df[["Price_in_Lakhs", "Area", "BHK", "Status"]],
    hue="Status",
    diag_kind="kde",
    palette="Set2",
    plot_kws={"alpha": 0.7, "s": 40, "edgecolor": "none"},
    diag_kws={"shade": True}
)

pair.fig.suptitle("Multivariate Relationship: Price, Area, BHK & Status", y=1.02)

plt.show()

Q1 = df['Price_in_Lakhs'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['Price_in_Lakhs'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

filtered_df = df[(df['Price_in_Lakhs'] >= Q1 - 1.5*IQR) &
                 (df['Price_in_Lakhs'] <= Q3 + 1.5*IQR)]

sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid", font_scale=1.2)
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))

sns.boxplot(
    x='Status',
    y='Price_in_Lakhs',
    data=filtered_df,
    palette='Set2',
    width=0.6
)

plt.title("Price Distribution by Status (Outliers Removed)", fontsize=14, pad=15)
plt.xlabel("Status", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Price (Lakhs)", fontsize=12)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
